headline: Pick ’n Save closing has Metcalfe Park neighbors worried about losing fresh food access
summary: The store is one of five Milwaukee-area Pick 'n Save supermarkets that will be closing. Its 2001 opening was a big boost for Metcalfe Park.

headline: Kroger (NYSE:KR) Announces Dividend Increase to US$1.40 Per Year
summary: Kroger (NYSE:KR) recently announced a dividend increase from $1.28 to $1.40 per year, with the next quarterly dividend of 35 cents per share set for September 2025. This positive development aligns with a robust 10% rise in Kroger's share price over the past week, significantly outperforming the market's 1.7% gain. headline: Kroger will close 60 stores nationwide. Are any Tennessee locations affected? What to know
summary: The Cincinnati-based supermarket giant announced the closure of these underperforming stores on June 20. The chosen locations will close over the next 18 months.

headline: Kroger's Board of Directors Raises Quarterly Dividend by 9%
summary: The Kroger Co.'s (NYSE: KR) Board of Directors approved a dividend increase from $1.28 to $1.40 per year. The next quarterly dividend of 35 cents per share will be paid on September 1, 2025, to shareholders of record as of close of business on August 15, 2025.
